@flexiarg coordination/mandatory-pur
@title Mandatory PUR (G1)
@keywords pur, validation, criteria, evaluation, outcome
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/proof-path futon-theory/stop-the-line]

! conclusion:
  If you want the system to produce organized knowledge, require a Pattern Use Record (PUR) that evaluates success criteria against produced artifacts.

  + context: Pattern selection only matters if we evaluate whether it worked.
  + IF:
    you want coordination outputs to be evidence-driven

  + HOWEVER:
    without PUR, you cannot distinguish successful pattern use from failure, drift, or luck

  + THEN:
    require G1 to emit a PUR for the PSR, and reject when criteria are not met

  + BECAUSE:
    this creates a stable learning signal for the library evolution loop

